{"type":"HOSTEL","name":"Adventure Inn Marahau","nameEN":"Adventure Inn Marahau","isActive":true,"isNew":false,"description":"Adventure Inn is a small backpackers which still has that custom New Zealand Bach (holiday home) feel to it!\r\n\r\nSituated just 300m from the beach front, and 750m from the entrance to the National Park. We have 8 bed dorm rooms, so you can relax and have a bit more comfort with out the chaos of your big urban backpackers. Your host is an ex backpacker bus tour guide with great knowledge and a passion for tourism.\r\n\r\nWe have loads of communal spaces to be used already including:\r\nMovie lounge\r\nPool tables\r\nDart boards\r\nFoosball\r\nTable Tennis\r\nCommunal Lounges\r\nIndoor and outdoor bbq table areas\r\nGiant bbq area\r\nLoads of outdoor grass space for sunbathing\r\nWinter time we have two fireplaces and heat pumps in the bedrooms\r\n\r\nWe are a place to relax and unwind. We want to distance ourselves from the mainstream backpackers that encourage partying and drinking, our vision is to become a place of rest and relaxation, to unwind from adventures to and from the National Park which is at our doorstep. \r\nWe do allow alcohol on site but in limited quantities. We have noise curfews in place to ensure our neighboring community also enjoys peace and quiet in our remote tranquil area. So if you want to get away from the bigger venues and find a place that is unique, a little quirky, yet clean, friendly and an atmosphere that creates a warm home away from home feeling then book a bed today! I suggest booking for three or four nights because once you get here you won't want to leave!\r\n\r\nIf you have any other queries please feel free to contact us.\r\n\r\n\r\nThursdays we love to encourage a group to attend the local evening cafe for open mic night!\r\n\r\nKiwi Experience passengers looking at staying with us from Kaiteriteri, you are able to organise a transfer from Kaiterteri via a couple of options:\r\n\r\nTapu Bay Shuttle